Change log for v0.1.9
================================

 - Layout performance improvements
 
 	Test for Popups/Layout PopupPanel:
 	
 		gwt-mosaic-0.1.8 Profile (6158.264ms, 197518 calls)
 		gwt-mosaic-0.1.9 Profile (3228.008ms, 111896 calls)

 - New Label & HTML widgets based on <label> tag instead of the default GWT widgets
 	http://code.google.com/p/gwt-mosaic/source/detail?r=662
 - WindowPanel new methods:
 	
 	public void setCaptionAction()
 	public void setCaptionAction(CaptionAction captionAction)
 	
 	where CaptionAction is: COLLAPSE, MAXIMIZE, NONE
 	
 	public boolean isHideContentsOnMove()
 	public void setCaptionAction(CaptionAction captionAction)
 	
 - Fix for: Issue 33 : WindowPanel issues in FireFox
 - WidgetWrapper implements HasAlignment
 - Layout popup panels & WindowPanel improvements
 	WIKI: http://code.google.com/p/gwt-mosaic/wiki/WindowPanel
 - Separator extends LayoutComposite and style changes
 - Fix for http://groups.google.com/group/gwt-mosaic/browse_thread/thread/f609dba8143f996b
 - Initial width & height of a widget is not ignored by the layout managers
 	http://code.google.com/p/gwt-mosaic/source/detail?r=600
 	
 	NOTE: this code will crash IE6, I put it in: if(!UserAgent.isIE6()){ ... }
 	
 - BorderLayout is using an invisible GlassPanel so that dragging a SplitBar widget over an IFRAME is possible
 	http://dev.gumboo.com:8880/gwt-mosaic/#CwBorderLayoutTest_Frames
 - Minimum size calculation fixed execpt of IE (since IE does not suppoer CSS min-width & min-height)
 - GWT Beans Binding update (SVN trunk), see: http://code.google.com/p/gwt-beans-
binding/source/detail?r=43
 - Fix for: Issue 35: Cannot use getWidgetIndex or  remove(Widget widget) in TabLayoutPanel
 - Actions API update because of layout changes  & Core modele cleanup

