Change log for v0.1.5
================================

 - Fix for:  Issue 15 : Issue with a WindowPanel , MessageBox login, and
MessageBox.alert
 - GridLayout getPreferredSize() bug fix
 - New ListBox widget: This widget is used to create a list of items where one or
more of the items may be selected. A ListBox may contain multiple columns.
modified.
 - HUMANIZED_MESSAGE z-index bug in GlassPanel fix
 - DoubleClick & ContextMenu support for ListBox
 - New widgets: LayoutPopupPanel & DecoratedLayoutPanel
 - WindowPanel, MessageBox & DropDownPanel update (they extend the new
DecoratedLayoutPopupPanel)
 - ComboBox is using the new ListBox widget (still not functional)
 - ScrollTreeTable extends ColumnWidget
 - New constructor added to create a LayoutPanel with the given element. The
element is presumed to be a <div>.
 - ScrollTable extends ColumnWidget, replaces GWT Incubator ScrollTable.
 - PagingScrollTable extends ColumnWidget, replaces GWT Incubator PagingScrollTable.
 - Fix for: http://groups.google.com/group/gwt-mosaic/browse_thread/thread/8db88fd8258e0ecd
 - Keyboard navigation in ListBox
 - Keyboard navigation for ListBox and ScrollTable/PaggingScrollTable
 - getFlowHeight() & getFlowWidth() bug fix for ListBox
 - Javadoc for FillLayout & LayoutManager update
 - Javadoc for BoxLayout, a minor BoxLayout bug fix and LayoutPanel update
 - BorderLayoutRegion enum renamed to Region
 - FormLayout widget based showcase demo update
 - Better initial size calculations for LayoutPanel placed in a widget that does
not implement HasLayoutManager like the RootPanel widget.
 - Documentation for layout managers added
 - ListBox widget (similar to ScrollTable but with a ListModel silimar to JList)
 - GWT Beans Binding integration & Showcase demo with a ListBox
 - Table widget (a PaggingScrollTable wrapper with a TableModel similar to JTable) 
 - CellEditors added in Table.
 - GWT Beans Binding v0.2.1 & GWTx upgrade